 For some problems, there may be more than one way to solve it. This explanation provides only one possible approach. Choose the method that is most clear and straightforward. To convert 50 minutes into hours:

$$
\begin{align*}
50 \text{ minutes} &= \frac{50}{60} \text{ hours}\\
&= \frac{5}{6} \text{ hours}
\end{align*}
$$

Final answer: $\frac{5}{6}$ hours.
